ReviewText: My girlfriend and I bought this coffee after sampling some on a plane journey! It has such a deep rich flavour and an immediate pick-me-up effect! Rarely a day goes by without a cup of Azera, either for when we are snuggled in front of the TV, or in the handy takeaway cups with swivel lid in the multipacks. Note. The only slight feedback I would give is, make sure you stir it well, as it can clump in the bottom of the mug. Otherwise, this is a cracking coffee!! :)
Title: Does what it say's on the tin! ;)

ReviewText: I think Nescafe hit the Jackpot with this coffee. It is by far the best coffee on the market at the minute. It is the closest coffee I have tasted that reflects freshly made coffee from a coffee shop. The aroma of Americano coffee is divine. I put the extra spoon of this coffee in my cup to get the maximum full flavoured aroma of the coffee. I like full bodied, rich aroma coffee and this has it in spades. I also love that crema effect when the hot water is poured. This appearance oozes freshness and aroma. Excellent coffee. Always have a spare tin in the cupboard. Always recommend this coffee to people.
Title: Converted Azera Coffee drinker

ReviewText:
I will actually add to this to make it a more substantial review.
My wife and I stumbled by accident on Azera a couple of years ago, and since then we haven't purchased any other brand of coffee. Azera tastes amazing its smooth but tastes like a freshly ground coffee. The fine granules make for a better coffee in my opinion. it is slightly more expensive than other brands but it's quality outweighs the price difference. plus opening a new tin of Azera is an experience in itself the aroma you get is second to none. Awesome!
Title: one word "Awesome"

ReviewText:
It's been a while since I tried this but the flavour was memorable for being slightly stronger than Nescafe original but with a much stronger aroma which gave an altogether more enjoyable drink. It's not too far to say it made drinking coffee an experience (a nice one at that) but the only downside is that the price reflects the exclusivity of the brand and so it's more often than not our of my budget. If you can afford it though it's well worth trying.
